FTIR interpretation uses the frequency–wavenumber relationship \(
u = c	ilde{
u}\), where \(	ilde{
u}\) is in cm\(^{-1}\). So \(
u = (3.0	imes 10^{10})(1700)=5.1	imes 10^{13}\ \mathrm{s^{-1}}\). A common mistake is using \(c=3.0	imes 10^8\ \mathrm{m\,s^{-1}}\) without converting 1700 cm\(^{-1}\) into m\(^{-1}\), causing a factor-of-100 error. Another error is treating wavenumber as wavelength directly, which inverts the relationship. ***
